HYPERTEXT PROTOCOL (HTTP,PORT 80)
HTTP is the protocol used to load websites.
Your browser sends a request to:
       IP of the server
       Port 80
Not encrypted 
Data is sent in plain text
Vulnerable to attacks (MITM, sniffing)

SECURE SHELL(SSH PORT 22)
SSH lets you securely connect to another computer remotely.
  ssh user@192.168.1.10
Encrypted communication 
Used by:
System admins
Hackers / pentesters
Gives command-line access to another machine
